<div class="problem"><p>Suppose that $A$ is an $m\times n$ matrix.  Define the linear transformation $T$ by
\begin{equation*}
\ltdefn{T}{\complex{n}}{\complex{m}},\quad \lt{T}{\vect{x}}=A\vect{x}
\end{equation*}
Prove that the kernel of $T$ equals the null space of $A$, $\krn{T}=\nsp{A}$.
</p></div>
